{"lemma":"مُجَرَّبٌ","slug":"مُجَرَّبٌ","root":"ج.ر.ب","root_slug":"ج-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5446"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"experienced, practiced, skilled"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of جَرَّبَ (jarraba, “to get wise by experience”)."},"ipa":["/mu.d͡ʒar.rib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5446","headword_ar":"مُجَرَّبٌ","root":"jrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has been tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, in affairs, and whose qualities have become known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has been tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved, and strengthened by experience in affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experienced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expert, in affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose qualities have been tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujar~ibN","text_ar":"مُجَرِّبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having experience in affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) In general, but not always, (MF,) the Arabs used the former of these two epithets [which are virtually synonymous]. (S, MF.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraAhimu mujar~abapN","text_ar":"دَرَاهِمُ مُجَرَّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weighed money."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almujar~abu","text_ar":"المُجَرَّبُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.)       -A2-  [It is also employed as an inf. n. of 2, in accordance with a usage of which there are many other instances; as in the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota EalaY Almujar~abi","text_ar":"اَنْتَ عَلَى المُجَرَّبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art about to have the proof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experience"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a prov., mentioned by AZ: said to him who asks respecting a thing which he is about to know of himself: originally said by a woman to a man who asked her an indecent question which he was himself about to resolve. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","TA","S","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}